# Force LF line endings for files that run inside the Linux container.
#
# Shell scripts with CRLF line endings fail at container startup with
# `/bin/sh^M: bad interpreter: No such file or directory` — a silent,
# total boot failure. The runtime image (python:3.13-slim) uses busybox
# sh. Pinning these to `eol=lf` guarantees the committed blob AND every
# checkout stays LF regardless of a contributor's git `core.autocrlf`
# setting (a Windows checkout would otherwise rewrite them to CRLF).
#
# Scoped intentionally narrow: only the files COPYed into and executed
# by the image. (The entrypoint is called out explicitly in addition to
# the *.sh glob as belt-and-suspenders / documentation of intent.)
*.sh text eol=lf
scripts/entrypoint.sh text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf
litestream.yml text eol=lf
